        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:08PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Downtown Asheville, or 4 miles southwest of Leicester,
moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Leicester and Canto.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
western North Carolina.</instruction>
